# Team hero layout (always)

Every team page header uses the **business-card** pattern. One block, one identity row.

## Structure

```
[cover photo — object-fit: cover, Live top-right]
[logo 50% on cover / 50% on white] [team name + subtitle + city]
[description · motto · social — below, with mt-3 spacing]
```

## Mandatory rules

- Logo **left**, text **right** — same row (`hero-card__identity`). Never center logo alone.
- Logo overlap: `margin-top: calc(var(--hero-logo-size) * -0.5 - var(--hero-logo-lift))` — center on cover edge (+10px lift).
- Use **container queries** on `.hero-card` (`team-hero`), not viewport `@media`.
- **Narrow (<540px):** logo **76px**, text `flex:1` (~80%), `align-items: center`.
- **Wide (≥540px):** logo **112px**, zone **25%**; **≥720px:** logo **120px**.
- Gap **13–15px**. Title 2 lines · subtitle/city 1 line each. Typography: name bold → subtitle light → city lightest.
- Logo: `MtsTeamLogo` + `mts-media-frame--logo-hero-card`, `object-fit: contain`, `z-index: 20`.
- Cover: `MtsCoverBanner`, fixed `--hero-cover-height`, `object-fit: cover`.
- Title: max **2 lines** + ellipsis. Subtitle/city: max **1 line** + ellipsis.

## Do not

- Stack title under logo on its own row
- Use `justify-center` on logo without text beside it
- Use `align-items: end` grid that pins logo to city line
- Invent new hero class names — extend `hero-card*` in `globals.css`
- Duplicate layout in builder preview — use `TeamHeroCard` / `BlockHero`

## Source files

- Component: `components/blocks/team-hero-card.tsx`
- Block wrapper: `BlockHero` in `components/blocks/all-blocks.tsx`
- Tokens: `lib/blocks/hero-layout.ts`
- Styles: `app/globals.css` (`.hero-card*`)
